subSubSection.paragraph:
Movements, Home range and Social organization.
The Napo Spiny-rat shifts its use of microhabitats during the flood season, moving into terra firma forests otherwise occupied by the Guyenne Spiny-rat (FP. 
guyannensis
) in southern Venezuela and northcentral Brazil or the Short-tailed Spiny-rat (
P. brevicauda
), Cuvier’s Spiny-rat (
P. cuvieri
), and Simons’s Spiny-rat in northern Peru.
